reviewText: One of the best actors of all times.  Too bad he died so young.  The movies he did make were fabulous. Casablanca!!!!!

Good insight on a man and the affect he had on hollywood! A must for fans of
Bogie!!! The guy left an impact
My daughter loves everything Bogart. They don't make them like him anymore. This is a great biography of his life.
Definitely a very talented actor and man.  He passed away in 1957 and people still talk about him.  He had that "it" quality.

It's a small documentary of 50 mins which gives a detailed insight into Bogart's film and personal life. Unfortunately, it does not have a single comment from Lauren though Bogie's son features often. Recommended for serious collectors and not for hobby purposes!
Bought this as a gift for my father-in-law for father's day. It came quickly and looked very nice. It was a good price as well. It was a nice addition to the other Bogart films that we bought him.
Very imformative biography on Humphrey Bogart. It brought out about his acting career and his life. I would recommend this to anyone who likes Humphrey Bogart.
